OL,3,CCharity run that barred women and
OL,4,Cgirls over 12 'reviewing its policies'
OL,6,FCertain exceptions under equality law
OL,7,Fcan apply to charities and religious
OL,8,Forganisations, including potentially
OL,9,Frestricting events to one sex only.
OL,11,FBut Muslim Women's Network UK said
OL,12,Fwhile single-sex charity runs can be
OL,13,Flegally permissible, organisers could
OL,14,Fhave taken "practical steps" such as
OL,15,Fdifferent starting times or separate
OL,16,Fgroups "to accommodate women and girls
OL,17,Fwithout compromising religious
OL,18,Fbeliefs".
